#Create day level averages for the data frame
agg.data<-aggregate(cbind(ideology, national.econ, personal.econ, PID, 
approve.bush, education, tv.campaign, radio.campaign, newspaper.campaign, 
internet.campaign, elect.mccain, old.mccain, obama.ideology, experience, 
judge, patriotic, values, dv, vote.2004, age, female, black, latino, incomeWW, education, non.white), list(date_c), mean, na.rm=TRUE)
t<-names(agg.data)
names(agg.data)<-c("date_c", t[2:27])

agg.data<-subset(agg.data, date_c!=20081007) #20081007 is not available in the NAES, so drop
agg.data<-subset(agg.data, date_c>20080604 & date_c<20081103) #Drop pre Obama observations
In [6]:
## Note: Below I estimate the five day averages, which is called movav.matrix. 
## The 27 in the loop is because there are 27 variables; 
## specifically, 27 cross section varying variables in the above data

movav.matrix<-matrix(NA, nrow=dim(agg.data)[1], ncol=dim(agg.data)[2])
		for(r in 2: 27){
			counter<-agg.data[,r]
				for(i in 1: length(counter)){
				counter[i]<-mean(c(counter[i], counter[i+1], counter[i+2], counter[i+3], counter[i+4]))
					}
 movav.matrix[,r]<-c(NA, NA, NA, NA, counter[1:145])
}


movav.matrix<-data.frame(agg.data[,1], movav.matrix[,2:27])
names(movav.matrix)<-paste(names(agg.data), "av", sep=".")

##Now, calculate d for every observation and difference appropriately using the movav.matrix

##drop missing values
movav.matrix<-movav.matrix[5:length(movav.matrix[,1]),] #Drop out
movav.matrix<-na.omit(movav.matrix) ##some "experience" observations don't appear until mid june

residual.matrix<-movav.matrix ##Create a matrix of residuals after differencing
for(i in 2:27){ #Loop through the moving average matrix, calculating Hurst, differenceing and filling in the residual matrix with differenced variables
			t<-hurstSpec(diff(movav.matrix[,i]),  method="standard", sdf.method="multitaper")
			dval<-t[1]+1-0.5
			d.val<-ifelse(dval<=1, dval, 1)
			residual.matrix[,i]<-diffseries(movav.matrix[,i], d.val)
			print(names(movav.matrix)[i])
			print(ifelse(dval<=1, "yes", "no"))
			print(dval)
}
names(residual.matrix)<-paste(names(agg.data), "res", sep=".")
